You still see some motorbikes, but they can’t match the speed of e-bike (see the photo below), some take around 20 mins to get to my office, while by e-bike it is 7 mins.

Bunch of e-bikes

Two years ago when I was researching for my project, the only commuting dominate that is fulling the buta majemuk (traffic jam) is tramvon. At that time I saw around 10 tramvon parked side by side in their dedicated parking space along Jalan Sudirman going from South Jakarta to my office in North Jakarta (about 6.5km). Now, it is rare to see them parked and their parking space are all empty.

Tramvon no longer singly dominates the commuting market. There two new modes:

Some companies now offer house-to-office shuttle service. The shuttle services is more common amongst the bigger multinational companies. The employees of PT. CliffCorp who are mainly engineers with upwards of 4 decades old use the shuttle, as do the predominantly software engineers from BarterLabs, Google, and PT.XYSY.
